2TGTsHlIu74s=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating testing requirements**\\n\\nI’m considering the existing classes, some of them aren’t public, which is an issue since all top-level classes need to be public. Maybe I should update the DdemlUtilInnerMessageLoopWrapperTest. The StandaloneDdeClient needs a separate file. There could be complications with Linux where uncaught exceptions in daemon threads might not fail processes. I also want to ensure that certain calls don’t lead to tests hanging, especially on non-Windows threads. I’ll verify supported behaviors without unnecessary waiting.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing test setup and behavior**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how the proxy metadata is generated and how its absence might cause a test failure in a native image. I don't need to edit existing metadata, but I should consider the dynamic proxy configuration for IDdeClient. If the test is under an agent, it won’t need direct reflection. \\n\\nIn the DdemlUtilInnerStandaloneDdeClientTest, I’m curious about adding final cleanup for Windows scenarios. If initialization fails, DDE could fail too, but I need to manage object closings carefully to avoid leaks.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering daemon settings and cleanup**\\n\\nI’m realizing I’ve set the daemon to true, but maybe closing resources is still recommended. I’m concerned about what happens if initialization fails. I need to ensure that resources are properly handled to avoid issues. Keeping things clean will be key here, especially because if the initialization doesn't go as planned, I don't want to leave anything hanging. It's a balance between setting the daemon and proper cleanup—definitely need to think this through!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_UPEfVyBo5OH8Jj4wpNNIs2bL|fc_077df666d49e7221016a10a89eef8881919b598a1aff75a321", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"class DdeAdapter|private final|new .*Callback|i